            <article>
                <header><h3>Making art with AI</h3></header>
                <p>This article is going to be a walk through of the process I used to make 
                  the pillar base portion of the art for this website.
                </p>
                <h4>Inspect: ankle??!</h4>
                <p>Because of the visual theme of the website being this "jack and the beanstalk"
                  type design, I had some challenges blending the bottom and the top with a trunk of variable length. 
                  To resolve that I used some clouds and water to cover the places where the top and the base 
                  would meet the trunk, which makes 5 vertical overlapping parts.</p>
                  <p>Maybe it is too much information, but if you inspect any page, you can see that the 5 parts are named
                    header, neck, body, leg, ankle, and footer.
                    The portion that sits above the footer would be the ankle, which is blended into the body using the leg.
                    The body is blended into the header using the neck, which sits just below the navigation links.
                  </p>
                  <p>For me it is super helpful to keep things organized if there is a mapping of the idea onto another concept, almost like an analogy.</p>
                  <h4></h4>
            </article>
          </section>
        </div>
      </section>
